-- BofA Says Housing Market Has ‘Clearly Begun to Turn a Corner’
-- B y   H u g h   S o n
-- 2012-10-17T11:41:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-17/bofa-says-housing-market-has-clearly-begun-to-turn-a-corner-.html
The U.S. housing market is starting
to improve, Bank of America Corp. Chief Financial Officer Bruce
Thompson said.  “We’ve clearly begun to turn a corner,” Thompson told
reporters on a conference call after the Charlotte, North
Carolina-based firm reported third-quarter earnings. “At the
same time you have to remain cautious because there are
headwinds out there.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
